 Johannesburg - Customs officials seized six boxes containing 80 000 Viagra pills, valued at almost R8 million, at OR Tambo International Airport on Thursday, the South African Revenue Service said in a statement on Friday. It is believed that the drugs, valued at R7 921 200 were part of a possible counterfeit footwear shipment that was detained on September 25. Upon inspection, SARS customs found 79 212 Viagra pills, along with 3 000 pairs of Adidas footwear. The goods were seized and will be handed over to police for further investigation. African News Agency